title: Salvatore Giuliano 1962
description: Salvatore Giuliano is a 1962 Italian film directed by Francesco Rosi. It is a documentary like film about the lives of those affected by the famous Sicilian bandit, Salvatore Giuliano, who doesn&#039;t appear directly in the film. Instead, real villagers were casted for most of the scenes. The narrative moves back and forth in time, including courtroom, crime and political issues.
